MAG5-60
The SureFire high-capacity magazine for 5.56x45 mm (.223 Remington) ammunition, also available in a 100-round version, is compatible with M4/M16/AR-15 variants and other firearms that accept standard STANAG 4179 magazines. Constructed from Mil-Spec hard-anodized aluminum, they feed smoothly and reliably due to optimal geometry, non-binding coil springs, and ingenious nesting polymer followers. The long-lasting springs are cadmium coated for low friction and excellent corrosion resistance. Magazines require no lubricants and can be easily disassembled without tools for cleaning.

SureFire High-Capacity magazines provide distinct tactical advantages: increased initial firepower in ambush situations; fewer reloads overall, which means less downtime and target distraction in a firefight; fast and easy magazine insertion, even with a closed bolt; less bulk compared to drum mags, enabling a normal weapon grip. The 60-round magazine—slightly thinner than two 30-round magazines clipped together and about the same overall length—fits in most dual magazine pouches, eliminating special carry pouches required for drum magazines.

Barretts BORS Information


LEAVE NOTHING TO CHANCE.
The Barrett Optical Ranging System (BORS) is an integrated ballistics computer that mounts directly on the riflescope and couples to the elevation knob.

BORS instantly takes care of the data work by drawing from several tables and taking into account a number of real-time external factors so you can focus on the task of achieving first round hits.

After determining the range to target, simply turn the elevation knob until the BORS screen matches your target's distance. Internal sensors automatically calculate the ballistic solution. BORS compensates for temperature and barometric pressure, calculates angle cosine and displays rifle cant.

Norman, REDACTED, $475 OBO
	Hey all, 
	I have available for trade/sale a sweet little Bullpup rifle. This is an EAA Appeal chambered in 2 Magnum. I love this rifle and would love to keep it, but another project has popped up and I really need to free up the funds. As such, im mainly looking for cash, but would consider trades if they were right. These are sweet little guns and are extremely compact. These are really hard to find and even harder to find in 22 magnum versus 22 long rifle. This shot great, but isn’t without its issues. It is missing both the front sight assembly and has had a picatinny type rail “creatively attached” to the rear area of the rifle. It isn’t the most glamorous installation, but it doesn’t look “bad” Either way, it could be removed if desired. This will come with the gun, the barrel extension/shroud, magazine, aftermarket rail, paperwork, and the factory case. The factory case is actually surprisingly nice
	These are awesome guns and are fully ambidextrous and can have the cocking lever and ejection port swapped to either side as desired. Would also consider most trades, but no BP’s, 22’s, or shotguns unless it is heavily in my favor. Other than that, just shoot me an offer,worst I can say is no. For any questions or offers, please shoot me a text at REDACTED or a message on here and we can go from there. Need to meet up in Norman on this if possible.

Thanks for looking and happy hunting!
